WEBVTT

00:00:01.933 --> 00:00:02.833
Now we have

00:00:02.833 --> 00:00:05.833
come to the Q&A section
of our presentation.

00:00:05.833 --> 00:00:08.200
We will address a few selected questions

00:00:08.200 --> 00:00:11.200
submitted by our attendees in the zoom
chat.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.700
The first question is,
what is the difference between an owner

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.800
and property owner.

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:21.166
This question addresses
the definition chapter of the code book.

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:24.700
So let's go to that slide.

00:00:28.466 --> 00:00:29.733
The owner refers

00:00:29.733 --> 00:00:33.433
to the entity that owns the portal pair,
whereas the property owner

00:00:33.433 --> 00:00:36.966
is the entity that owns the property
where a portal is installed.

00:00:37.666 --> 00:00:40.500
This means that a portal pair
can have the same

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:43.366
or different property
owners for each portal

00:00:43.366 --> 00:00:45.266
within that pair.

00:00:45.266 --> 00:00:49.300
A frequent follow up
question is about the change in ownership.

00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:53.833
So if the owner of the property changes,
it has to be notified

00:00:53.833 --> 00:00:57.600
to us, the Department of Portals
within one month of the change.

00:00:58.333 --> 00:01:01.333
You can do this through the manufacturer's
phone application

00:01:01.633 --> 00:01:06.200
or visit the DOP office in person,
providing the necessary materials.

00:01:07.266 --> 00:01:09.066
If the owner changes,

00:01:09.066 --> 00:01:13.300
meaning that the portal payer
is either sold or gifted to someone else,

00:01:13.733 --> 00:01:16.566
you simply have to follow
the application process,

00:01:16.566 --> 00:01:19.566
which is also available on the app
or in person.

00:01:20.533 --> 00:01:23.733
If a portal is being migrated,
in which case it's

00:01:23.733 --> 00:01:26.066
the property owner that could change.

00:01:26.066 --> 00:01:29.233
You typically submit
a migration request from the app

00:01:29.533 --> 00:01:33.433
and the manufacturer will take care
of the migration and information update.

00:01:34.600 --> 00:01:36.700
Another frequently asked question is

00:01:36.700 --> 00:01:39.700
how to repair a disconnected portal.

00:01:39.833 --> 00:01:41.833
If we go to the slide where defines

00:01:41.833 --> 00:01:47.000
the difference between deactivation and disconnection...

00:01:50.933 --> 00:01:52.566
As we can see,

00:01:52.566 --> 00:01:55.700
that disconnection,
which happens in the case of an emergency

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:58.700
shutdown, ends
the life of the portal aperture pair.

00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:02.700
The only way to repair
this is to replace the aperture pair.

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:05.533
For many newer models of portal,

00:02:05.533 --> 00:02:09.100
the manufacturer can ship aperture
replacement particles to you.

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:11.433
After proper
inspection of the frame condition.

00:02:12.433 --> 00:02:13.533
If the frame

00:02:13.533 --> 00:02:16.766
is damaged in a way
that makes it unable to function properly,

00:02:17.133 --> 00:02:20.600
or if you have an older model
that doesn't support aperture

00:02:20.600 --> 00:02:23.600
replacement, you will have to schedule
a frame replacement,

00:02:23.766 --> 00:02:27.033
which entails the uninstallation
of the disconnected portal frames

00:02:27.566 --> 00:02:30.533
and installation of a replacement
portal pair.

00:02:30.533 --> 00:02:33.533
This process usually takes several months.

00:02:34.766 --> 00:02:38.866
All the above will be taken care of
by the manufacturer if proper insurance

00:02:38.866 --> 00:02:43.200
is in place, and any changes
in information such as damage report,

00:02:43.766 --> 00:02:46.566
activation date will be updated by either

00:02:46.566 --> 00:02:49.566
the inspector or the manufacturer.

00:02:49.666 --> 00:02:51.866
And that concludes our presentation.

00:02:51.866 --> 00:02:55.100
If you have any further questions,
either for the Department of Portals

00:02:55.433 --> 00:02:59.166
or for our licensed manufacturer,
you can submit them online

00:02:59.166 --> 00:03:02.133
or through our call center.
Thank you all for your attending.

